dct_title_s: Toshien / prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (A<).
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals. Place names are transcribed according to the Modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. Name has changed to Tso-ying [Tsoying]. Map shows prefecture, gun and kai boundaries,roads, trails, three classes of railroads, water features, areas of vegetation and cultivation, walls, high-tension power lines, mills, fences, cemeteries, built-up areas, other populated places and some individual buildings are named. "Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system." Includes glossary, index to boundaries, coverage diagram, and grid data.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1944.
Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
